      "date": "2011-03-10 06:00:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe patch does not resolve the issue.\n\nI saw some codes in test-framework.sh also generated the yml files named with $(hostname), like:\n\ncheck_logdir() {\n    ......\n    else\n        touch $dir/node.$(hostname).yml\n    fi\n    return 0\n}\n\nAnd in auster, the log file name was defined as:\nlog_name=${suite_name}.suite_log.$(hostname).log\n\nIt's likely there are other files which also use $(hostname) or $HOSTNAME.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
